  "ai_usage": "Use to add tactile grain over flat fills, gradients, and mesh backgrounds (kills banding, adds a premium analog feel). Generate noise with feTurbulence(type='fractalNoise', baseFrequency ~0.8, numOctaves~3); render it to a full-size rect; place that as a position:fixed/absolute overlay at low opacity (0.04-0.08), pointer-events:none, above the background but below text. Do NOT animate the turbulence (costly) — a static layer is enough. Optionally desaturate it with feColorMatrix.",
  "path": "effects/svg-effects/svg-noise-texture.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>SVG Grain / Noise Texture</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"svg-noise-texture\",\n    \"title\": \"SVG Grain / Noise Texture\",\n    \"summary\": \"A subtle film-grain overlay generated entirely by feTurbulence — no image asset.\",\n    \"description\": \"feTurbulence produces fractal noise rendered to a rect, used as a low-opacity overlay to add tactile grain over flat colors and gradients (the trendy 'noise' texture), with zero network cost.\",\n    \"theme\": \"svg-effects\",\n    \"categories\": [\"svg\", \"filter\", \"texture\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"svg\", \"noise\", \"grain\", \"feturbulence\", \"texture\", \"film\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"svg\", \"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All modern browsers (feTurbulence).\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Generating noise once is cheap; do NOT animate it (re-rendering noise every frame is expensive). Reuse one noise layer as a fixed overlay.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Purely decorative; keep opacity low so it never reduces text contrast. No motion.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"baseFrequency\", \"description\": \"Grain size (higher = finer)\", \"default\": \"0.8\" },\n      { \"name\": \"overlay opacity\", \"description\": \"Grain intensity\", \"default\": \"0.06\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Colored grain (skip the desaturating matrix)\", \"Heavier grain for a poster look\", \"Scope the overlay to one card\"],\n    \"related\": [\"svg-turbulence-distortion\", \"mesh-gradient\", \"aurora-background\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use to add tactile grain over flat fills, gradients, and mesh backgrounds (kills banding, adds a premium analog feel). Generate noise with feTurbulence(type='fractalNoise', baseFrequency ~0.8, numOctaves~3); render it to a full-size rect; place that as a position:fixed/absolute overlay at low opacity (0.04-0.08), pointer-events:none, above the background but below text. Do NOT animate the turbulence (costly) — a static layer is enough. Optionally desaturate it with feColorMatrix.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }\n    body { position: relative; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7c5cff, #2dd4bf 60%, #f0abfc); font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }\n    .stage { position: absolute; inset: 0; display: grid; place-items: center; color: #fff; text-align: center; }\n    .stage h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; margin: 0; text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.3); }\n    .grain {\n      position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; opacity: .07; mix-blend-mode: overlay;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <svg class=\"grain\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    <filter id=\"noise\">\n      <feTurbulence type=\"fractalNoise\" baseFrequency=\"0.8\" numOctaves=\"3\" stitchTiles=\"stitch\" />\n      <feColorMatrix type=\"saturate\" values=\"0\" />\n    </filter>\n    <rect width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" filter=\"url(#noise)\" />\n  </svg>\n  <div class=\"stage\"><h1>Grain over gradient</h1></div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
